# Post-Mortem: dflash 27B DFlash perf regression + recovery (2026-04-26)

**Status:** RESOLVED. Default canonical perf restored on `dflash`. Pending cherry-pick to `master`.

**TL;DR:** A four-day perf regression on `dflash` traced to two compounding issues: (1) PR #32 (`cleanup/dead-wmma-kernels`) on master removed three WMMA kernel files + dispatch entries that were load-bearing, doubling per-cycle cost on 27B DFlash verify; (2) `HIPFIRE_NORMALIZE_PROMPT` was an undocumented major perf lever (+24% τ on PEP-8 prompts) that defaulted OFF, so even unregressed code appeared 24% slower than memory's "200+ tok/s" recollection. Recovery: confirm GPU clean → checkout pre-merge engine → revert merge → cherry-pick remaining valuable master fixes → flip `prompt_normalize` default to ON. Final 27B-3.5 LRU code DFlash @ max=120 = **199 tok/s τ=10.36** (vs prior session's "WTF" 95 tok/s).

---

